 * to prevent overlapping WP-Cron spawns on horizontally-scaled environments
 * where multiple application servers may simultaneously trigger a cron run.
 * The lock name is derived from `wp_hash( $lock_name . ABSPATH )` truncated
 * to 64 characters to comply with MySQL lock name limits. If GET_LOCK()
 * is unavailable (e.g. on PostgreSQL via HyperDB), falls back to a
 * transient-based semaphore with microsecond-precision timestamps.
 *
 * @since 5.7.0
 * @access private
